# Tree Structure & Slices

## Two Slice Systems (Don't confuse them)

| System | Function | Used for |
|--------|----------|---------|
| **Flow slices** | `getFlowSlices(tree)` | Simulation ordering in `computeFlowRates` |
| **Display slices** | `getDisplaySlices(tree)` | Visual columns in `TreeLevelSlices` UI |

`getDisplaySlices` buckets nodes by `displaySliceIndex ?? defaultFromMap`.  
Default display slice matches the flow slice, so they start in sync.

`resolveSupplierIds` and hover lineage (`getRelatedNodeIdsForHover`) treat recipe byproducts as real outputs, so hover/pin on consumers (e.g. residual fuel) includes byproduct producers and their upstream source chain.

## Structural Relationships
- Parent → child: `children: TreeNode[]` arrays (canonical structure)
- Child → parent: `parentId` string
- Use `findNode(tree, id)` to locate a node, `replaceNode(tree, newNode)` to update it

## Key Mutation Functions — `src/lib/flowChartTree.ts`
```ts
replaceNode(tree, newNode)               // immutable swap by id
reorderSiblingBefore(tree, parentId, activeId, insertBeforeId)
moveNodeDisplaySlice(tree, parentId, activeId, targetSliceIdx, insertBeforeId)
reorderNodeInColumn(tree, activeId, insertBeforeId, colIds)
getDisplaySlices(tree)                   // → TreeNode[][]
getRelatedNodeIdsForHover(tree, id)      // → Set<string>
```

## Key Mutation Functions — `src/lib/flowChartTreeMutations.ts`
```ts
addChildToNode(tree, parentId, newNode, insertAtIndex?, inputEdges?, displaySliceIndex?)
updateNodeInTree(tree, nodeId, patch)
synthesizeMissingInputEdges(tree)       // rebuild inputEdges from structure
recalcTree(tree)                        // recompute totalOutput on every node
mergeNodesAsChild / splitMergedNode
```

## Standard Mutation Wrapper
```ts
setTree((t) => recalcTree(synthesizeMissingInputEdges(mutate(t))));
```

## `displaySliceIndex`
- Purely a display hint — does **not** affect flow simulation
- `moveNodeDisplaySlice` updates it and pins siblings to same column
- The root node's `displaySliceIndex` can be changed (non-extractor roots only)

## Transport Keys on Edges
- `incomingBeltKey` / `inputEdges[].beltKey` can hold either conveyor (`belt*`) or pipeline (`pipe*`) keys.
- `updateAllBeltsInTree` applies global belt tier only to solid-item links; fluid links keep/normalize to pipe tiers.
